In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 3, 2012, as Labor Day and emphasizes the importance of the American labor force. He acknowledges the contributions and resilience of working men and women, highlighting the achievements and rights that were won through the efforts of labor unions. Obama expresses his commitment to preserving collective bargaining rights and ensuring fair pay, safe working conditions, and a secure retirement for American workers. He recognizes the challenges the nation faces but remains confident in the strength and innovation of the American workforce to overcome them. Obama calls upon public officials and the people of the United States to observe Labor Day with programs and activities that honor working Americans.